1. Get domain name and bind to host server ip addresss.

type myip at google to get host server ip address 73.76.111.140. 
pay domain name www.mixwellsoftware.com 1$/m at 101domain.com. 
login 101domain.com em_dl00 to set Domain Names\mixwellsfotware.com\DNS Records\Manage Advanced Domain Record Settings (CNAME, A, MX).
add/edit record mixwellsoftware.com Record and www.mixwellsoftware.com to 73.76.111.140 and click submmit.

2. Set Root to forward internet ip address to local host server addresss. 
at host pc to expore 192.168.0.1 admin dl00 to my router TP-LINK setup
At Network tab: to makesure IP address 73.76.111.140 
At Forwarding tab: add visutal servers port=80 IP address 192.168.0.109 (get from ipconfig at PC).
At Forwarding tab: add visutal servers port=21 IP address 192.168.0.109. Common Service Port: FTP.
At Forwarding tab: add visutal servers port=161 IP address 192.168.0.109. Common Service Port: POP3.

ping http://73.76.111.140 for http://mixwellsoftware.com

3. set web page at pc webroot.
C:\inetpub\wwwroot is my pc default web server root site.
http://localhost get ip address run ipconfig => ip = 192.168.0.109.

save a index.html file at C:\inetpub\wwwroot as start web page.

or
create C:\inetpub\wwwroot\Web.xml file to set this foder as web stie.

<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<configuration>
    <system.webServer>
        <defaultDocument>
            <files>
                <remove value="index.aspx" />
                <add value="index.aspx" />
            </files>
        </defaultDocument>
        <directoryBrowse enabled="true" />
    </system.webServer>
</configuration>

may need set IIS manager/Features View/Directory Browsing/Actions/Enable.

go to iis manager


right click BPWEN-PC\hwang822\Sites\Add Web sites...
Site name: Default Web Site. Applicaiton pool: DefalultAppPool. Physical path: %SystemDrive%\inetpub\wwwroot. Type: http. Port: 80. Click: OK. 
select BPWEN-PC\hwang822\Sites\Default Web Site\Manager WebSit\Start or Stop or Restart.
select BPWEN-PC\hwang822\Sites\Default Web Site\Manager WebSit\Browse.
create  at C:\inetpub\wwwroot

4. Add Web Services at www.mixwellsoftware.com
   a. using MS Visual Studio to create mvc application MixwellMvc project. 
      build\publish MixwellMvc project to C:\inetpub\wwwroot\MixwellMvc.
      ie type www.mixwellsoftware.com\mixwellmvc to test web page.


   b. using MS Visual Studio to create web application MixwellWeb (asp.net webform) project.
      build\publish MixwellWeb project to  C:\inetpub\wwwroot\MixwellWeb.
      ie type www.mixwellsoftware.com\mixwellweb to test web page.

   b. using MS Visual Studio to create web application MixwellWcf.
      build\publish MixwellWcf project to  C:\inetpub\wwwroot\MixwellWcf.
      ie type www.mixwellsoftware.com\mixwellwcf to test web page.
      
4. Add FTP services at www.mixwellsoftware.com
Go to control pannel/Programs/Programs and Features/Turn Windows features on ofr off.
Turn On Internet Information Service (iis) FTP Server/FTP Extensibility/FTP Service, OK.

Go to iis manager.
right click BPWEN-PC\hwang822\Sites\Add FDP sites...
FTP Site Name: Default Ftp Site. 
Content Directory: C:\inetpub\wwwroot. (could be any where, set C:\inetpub\wwwroot to remote update web codes).
Next
Binding IP Address: 192.168.0.109, Port: 21.
Check Start FTP site autmatically.
SSL: No SSL
Next.
Authentication: Basic. Allow access: Apecified users (default using system user username and password).
Next.

using file exporlare 
type in ftp://192.168.0.109, un: gm, pw: dl31
Turn of ftp server at firewall.

download and install FileZilla
host: www.mxiwellsoftware.com
un: gm
pw: dl31

5. setup email server at host.
    go to http://www.hmailserver.com and down load the email server.
    add domain mixwellsoftware.com.  add account hwang@mixwellsoftware.com
   
    SMTP stands for Simple Mail Transfer Protocol. SMTP is used when email is delivered from an email client, such as Outlook Express, to an email server or when email is delivered from one email server to another. SMTP uses port 25. 
    POP3 stands for Post Office Protocol. POP3 allows an email client to download an email from an email server. The POP3 protocol is simple and does not offer many features except for download. Its design assumes that the email client downloads all available email from the server, deletes them from the server and then disconnects. POP3 normally uses port 110.
    IMAP stands for Internet Message Access Protocol. IMAP shares many similar features with POP3. It, too, is a protocol that an email client can use to download email from an email server. However, IMAP includes many more features than POP3. The IMAP protocol is designed to let users keep their email on the server. IMAP requires more disk space on the server and more CPU resources than POP3, as all emails are stored on the server. IMAP normally uses port 143. Here is more information about IMAP. 
   
    MX is an abbreviation for Mail Exchanger and is used by all mail servers when they send an email.
    
